"metaSummary_en": "Mega Altaria ex Espeon is still by far the most played deck (7.56% usage) but caps at 50.46% win rate; the best genuinely playable win rate belongs to Mega Manectric ex Zeraora (52.03%, 2% usage), ahead of Suicune ex Baxcalibur (51.86%), Mega Altaria ex Gourgeist (51.56%) and Mega Blaziken ex Greninja (51.37%). The meta stays almost frozen on the B3a (Paradox Drive) data, still dominated by Mega decks and Magnezone/Miraidon variants, because Everyday Wonders (B3b) tournaments only count 178 players so far; the only notable top-10 shift is Magnezone Miraidon ex and Mega Blaziken ex Greninja swapping the 5th and 6th spots. Early B3b tournaments already hint at new faces (Miraidon ex Magnezone on top, then Mega Sableye ex Darkrai ex, Meowscarada ex and Mega Gardevoir ex Mega Diancie ex boosted by the new set), while the high-win-rate outsiders to watch are Jolteon ex Jolteon (52.83%, best win rate of the format), Mega Altaria ex Greninja (52.79%) and Iron Valiant Iron Boulder (52.67%). Hot news: the Everyday Wonders mini-expansion (B3b), led by Mega Diancie ex, has been live since June 29; July lines up the Everyday Wonders Emblem Event, Community Week, a Growlithe/Emolga Wonder Pick and the Hisuian Zorua Drop Event, before the major Ruler of the Skies expansion (B4, July 30, Mega Rayquaza ex).",
